snippet.textDisplay:
China was told to close all wet markets that keep and sell live animals 18 years ago, probably not the first time. So why China was and still is reluctant to do so? Wildlife trade (quintessentially poaching!) is one of the biggest & most profitable businesses in the world. Millions of people are involved in it globally, of course the huge profit is not shared equally. Yes, it greatly affects the Chinese economy.
Let's not forget that selling bush meat is only a fraction of this lucrative business but poses the greatest health hazard. The biggest part is selling all kinds of animal parts, legally or illegaly, and this trafficking and trading largely controlled by China and some other Southeast Asian countries.
